                <p>Mafia: The Old Country is launching a week from today on August 8. In an effort to make sure players are ready for its release, 2K has revealed the game’s global unlock times. They all center on a late Thursday or early Friday morning, with slight changes based on time zone and platform; in some cases, Mafia: The Old Country will be made available on PC/Steam before console and vice versa.</p><p>When it comes to the US, the PC version is always unlocked first. Those residing on the west coast will get to play Mafia: The Old Country starting as early as 9 AM PT on August 7, with the central and eastern time zones following suit at 11 AM CT and 12 PM ET respectively. Console players will have till wait a bit longer; the PS5 and Xbox Series X|S versions will become available on August 7 at 9 PM PT, 11 PM CT and 12 AM ET (on August 8).</p>



    
